Step 1: Install Requirements

Install the following in your system:

Node.js

VS Code

Check installation in terminal:

node -v
npm -v
Step 2: Create Project Folder

Create a folder:

CourseEnrollmentProject

Inside create two folders:

CourseEnrollmentProject
│
├── backend
└── frontend
Step 3: Create Backend Server

Go inside backend folder.

Open terminal and run:

npm init -y

Install required packages:

npm install express cors

Now create files:

backend
│
├── server.js
└── students.json
Step 4: Add Backend Code

Paste the server.js code inside:

backend/server.js

Create students.json

backend/students.json

Add:

[]
Step 5: Run Backend Server

In backend terminal run:

node server.js

You will see:

Server running on http://localhost:5000

Leave this terminal running.

Step 6: Create React Frontend

Open a new terminal.

Go to project folder:

cd CourseEnrollmentProject

Create React app:

npx create-react-app frontend

Move into frontend:

cd frontend
Step 7: Install Axios

Axios is used to call API.

Run:

npm install axios
Step 8: Add React Code

Open:

frontend/src/App.js

Delete old code and paste the React App.js code.

Save the file.

Step 9: Run React Application

In frontend folder run:

npm start

React will start at:

http://localhost:3000
Step 10: Test the Application

Open browser

Enter:

Name
Email
Course

Click Enroll

You will see:

Course Enrolled Successfully
Step 11: Check Stored Data

Open:

backend/students.json

